#compdef age-plugin-sntrup761x25519
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# keisentraut/age-plugin-sntrup761x25519 src/main.rs —
#   `struct PluginOptions` at lines 303-314 (the StructOpt
#     derive struct with 1 flag)
#   main() at lines 316-344 (the dispatch: --age-plugin runs
#     the state machine; no-arg invocation generates a new
#     identity)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# age-plugin-sntrup761x25519 is the **post-quantum-safe age
# plugin** using the sntrup761 KEM (Streamlined NTRU Prime)
# from libpqcrypto, combined with X25519 for hybrid
# encryption.  The same KEM that OpenSSH uses for its
# `sntrup761x25519-sha512` PQ-secure key exchange.  Sister to
# R228's age-plugin-fido2-hmac (which also supports a PQ mode
# via `--post-quantum` but with FIDO2-token-bound keys
# instead of file-based identities).
#
# Critical extraction note: age-plugin-sntrup761x25519 has the
# **MINIMAL VIABLE age-plugin CLI surface** — only 1 flag:
# `--age-plugin STATE_MACHINE` (the standard age-plugin
# protocol entry point).  When invoked WITHOUT this flag, the
# binary generates a new random identity + recipient pair to
# stdout (main.rs:331-342) — no flags needed for the most
# common user-facing workflow.
#
# Critical extraction note: this is **the corpus's contrast
# example** to R228's age-plugin-fido2-hmac (10 flags).  Both
# implement the same age-plugin protocol but expose vastly
# different surfaces:
#   - fido2-hmac: 10 flags, 3 invocation patterns, env-var
#                 overrides — because FIDO2 token interaction
#                 has many knobs (algorithm choice, symmetric
#                 vs asymmetric, magic identity, etc.)
#   - sntrup761:  1 flag, 1 invocation pattern — because the
#                 PQ KEM has no user-facing parameters (the
#                 algorithm choice is in the binary name)
# This documents that age-plugin authors have FULL latitude in
# CLI design — only the `--age-plugin STATE_MACHINE` protocol
# entry point is required.
#
# Critical extraction note: sntrup761x25519 uses **structopt**
# (the historical clap-derive predecessor; replaced by clap
# v3's #[derive(Parser)] in 2022).  Both APIs are
# behaviorally equivalent for completion purposes — same
# auto-generated --help and --version.

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help and exit (structopt auto-injected)]' \
  '(-V --version)'{-V,--version}'[show version and exit (structopt auto-injected)]' \
  '--age-plugin=[plugin state machine (called by age itself; users should NOT invoke directly)]:state-machine:'
